'''''Rookies: Day Long Remembered''''' was the planned third [[Star Wars comic books|webstrip]] of the [[Rookies (webstrips)|''Rookies'']] series. It is to be written by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and was set to begin in [[2008]]. Along with [[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed (webstrip)|''The Force Unleashed'' webstrip]], it was originally announced as being available for free on [[StarWars.com]],<ref>{{WordPress|subdomain=starwarsblog|url=2007/05/27/webstrip-chatter-at-celebration-iv/#more-57|name=Celebration IV|text=Webstrip Chatter|archivedate=20230427013915}}</ref> but was later revealed to be a [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] exclusive.<ref name="SWArchive-Hyperspace 2008: A Taste of What's to Come">{{SWArchive|url=hyperspace/about/news/news20080116.html|text=Hyperspace 2008: A Taste of What's to Come}}</ref> Hyperspace was shut down in [[2011]].<ref name="Hyperspace 2011">{{SWArchive|url=fans/news/hyperspace2010/index.html|text=Last Chance to Order the 2010 Hyperspace Member Kit!}}</ref> In [[2025]], Hidalgo confirmed that a script was written.<ref name="Pablo">{{Bluesky|infinata.bsky.social|post/3lxjarpgkns2e|[[Pablo Hidalgo]]|date=2025-08-29|quote=Rookies had a script. Don't recall anything on the TFU front.|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/npK7g|archivefile=File:PabloHidalgo-RookiesScript-Bluesky.png}} {{C|In response to: "@infinata.bsky.social Were any of the TFU or Rookies: DLR webstrips ever written, or only got into the concept stages?"}}</ref> However, as of {{CURRENTYEAR}}, the webstrip has not yet been published nor officially canceled.

